#compdef mmdr
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# mmdr — fast Mermaid diagram renderer in pure Rust (Rust, 1,369★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/1jehuang/mermaid-rs-renderer
# author : 1jehuang
# license: MIT
# binary : `mmdr` — the mermaid-rs-renderer CLI; no Node/browser
#          dependency (vs mermaid-cli which spawns a headless Chrome).
#          Claimed 100-1400× faster than mermaid-cli for the same
#          diagram type set (23 diagram types supported).
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from src/cli.rs
# on the 1jehuang/mermaid-rs-renderer v0.2.2 tip — clap-derive `Args`
# struct with `#[arg(short, long, default_value_t, value_parser)]`
# attributes parsed exactly as declared.  Note that the long-flag style
# is camelCase (e.g. `--outputFormat`, `--preferredAspectRatio`,
# `--nodeSpacing`, `--fastText`, `--dumpLayout`) to match the upstream
# mermaid-cli flag naming convention.
#
# Direct deps from Cargo.toml (selected):
#   resvg            0.47.0  (optional, default-on via `png` feature)
#   usvg             0.47.0  (optional, default-on via `png` feature)
#                            ← canonical Rust pure-language SVG renderer
#                              (this axis) — by Yevhenii Reizner
#                              (RazrFalcon/resvg) at the linebender-
#                              adjacent open-source graphics ecosystem;
#                              pure-Rust SVG parser (`usvg`) + SVG
#                              renderer (`resvg`) producing PNG output
#                              without shelling out to librsvg/Inkscape/
#                              Chrome.  Same author behind ttf-parser +
#                              fontdb + svgtypes + tiny-skia — the
#                              entire pure-Rust 2D graphics stack.
#   fontdb           0.23    (Yevhenii Reizner's font database for
#                              system + embedded font discovery)
#   ttf-parser       0.25    (Yevhenii Reizner's pure-Rust TTF/OTF
#                              parser — the canonical Rust TrueType
#                              implementation, used by resvg, swash,
#                              cosmic-text, vello, every modern Rust
#                              text renderer)
#   json5            1.3     (JSON5 parser — Mermaid uses JSON5 for
#                              themeVariables config)
#   regex + serde + serde_json + once_cell + anyhow + thiserror
#   clap (derive)            (CLI parser, behind the `cli` feature)
#
# mmdr renders Mermaid diagram syntax (flowchart, sequence, class,
# state, gantt, pie, ER, etc. — 23 diagram types) directly to SVG or
# PNG without any browser dependency.  Reads Mermaid source from a
# .mmd file, from stdin (`-i -`), or extracts code blocks from
# Markdown if `--input file.md`.  Layout via internal graph
# algorithms (no Graphviz/dagre dependency); rendering via the
# resvg+usvg pure-Rust SVG pipeline.  Configurable via Mermaid-style
# themeVariables JSON5 config file.
#
# === AXIS 179 OPENER — pure-language SVG renderers ======================
# Axis position: Rust=234 OPENS Axis 179 at slot 1/0/0.  Canonical Rust
# pure-language SVG library is `resvg` + `usvg` by Yevhenii Reizner
# (RazrFalcon at github.com/RazrFalcon) — pure-Rust SVG 1.1 parser
# (`usvg` simplifies the SVG tree into a normalized form) and renderer
# (`resvg` rasterizes via tiny-skia to PNG / RGBA pixel buffers).  No
# librsvg/Cairo/Inkscape/Chrome dependency; pure-Rust from parse
# through font shaping (via Yevhenii's ttf-parser + fontdb) through
# raster output.  Used by mmdr (this CLI), kornia-rs computer vision,
# the @resvg/resvg-js npm WASM port, and most modern Rust tools that
# need SVG → bitmap conversion without a system C library.
#
# Cycle position in current 3+1 micro-cycle:
#   Rust=234     ← THIS FILE              (axis 179 OPENS, slot 1/0/0)
#   Go=234       ← next round              (axis 179 continues, slot 2/0/0)
#   TS-Node=234  ← round after             (axis 179 CLOSES at triple-234, slot 1/1/1)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

_mmdr() {
    _arguments -s \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[print help]' \
        '(- *)'{-V,--version}'[print version]' \
        '(-i --input)'{-i,--input=}'[input file (.mmd) or `-` for stdin]:input file:_files -g "*.(mmd|MMD|md|MD)"' \
        '(-o --output)'{-o,--output=}'[output file (svg/png); defaults to stdout for SVG if omitted]:output file:_files -g "*.(svg|SVG|png|PNG)"' \
        '(-e --outputFormat)'{-e,--outputFormat=}'[output format (default svg)]:format:(svg png)' \
        '(-c --configFile)'{-c,--configFile=}'[config JSON5 file with Mermaid-like themeVariables]:config:_files -g "*.(json|json5|JSON|JSON5)"' \
        '(-w --width)'{-w,--width=}'[output width in pixels (default 1200)]:pixels:' \
        '(-H --height)'{-H,--height=}'[output height in pixels (default 800)]:pixels:' \
        '--preferredAspectRatio=[output aspect ratio (`width:height`, `width/height`, or decimal)]:ratio:' \
        '--nodeSpacing=[node spacing in pixels]:pixels:' \
        '--rankSpacing=[rank spacing in pixels (between layout layers)]:pixels:' \
        '--dumpLayout=[dump computed layout JSON to file (or directory for markdown input)]:layout dump:_files' \
        '--timing[output timing information as JSON to stderr]' \
        '--fastText[use fast text metrics (approximate widths) for speed]'
}

_mmdr "$@"
